# Admin UI/UX rulebook (mandatory — read before any UI change)

Read [`docs/DESIGN_SYSTEM.md`](../../docs/DESIGN_SYSTEM.md) once. This file is **always applied** in Cursor. Complete the pre-ship checklist (§11) before marking UI work done.

Target: **14" laptop (~1366×768)**. Feel like Linear / Stripe / Ramp — dense, alive, single-viewport.

---

## 1. Foundations

- **Styling**: shadcn semantic tokens + `@/components/ui/*`.
- **Product layout**: `@/components/app/*` (`AppPage`, `AppListCard`, `AppModalFooter`, …).
- **Polaris**: information architecture only. Never for colors or typography.
- **Cards**: `rounded-xl border-border shadow-sm`.
- **Tables**: `TABLE_HEAD_CLASS` on every `TableHead`.

---

## 2. Density — fits one viewport

- Inputs / selects / triggers: **`h-9`**. Never `h-10`/`h-11`.
- Card padding: **`p-4`**. Modal body: **`px-5 py-4`**, **`space-y-3`**.
- Dialog width: **`w-[min(1200px,96vw)]`**.

**Vertical budget (footer-first modals — see §7):**
Footer ≈ 72px + 14" usable ≈ 720px ⇒ body must fit in **≈ 648px**. **Inner scroll in a modal = failure.**

---

## 3. Layout

- Pack identity fields on **one row** (avatar + name + phone + civil id + employee id + driver id).
- Side-by-side cards: **`lg:items-stretch`** + **`h-full`** — no half-empty card.
- Documents / assets: **`lg:grid-cols-4`** on desktop.
- Helper text: **`text-[10px]`** inline; hide when redundant.

### Standard spacing (mandatory — import `@/components/app/layout-spacing`)

| Token | Class | Use |
|-------|-------|-----|
| Command page inset | `LAYOUT.commandPageInsetNegate` on route layout | Live tracking, maps — reduces default `main p-6` to effective **12px** |
| Panel gap | `LAYOUT.panelGap` (`gap-2`) | Sidebar ↔ main stage in split command layouts |
| Stack gap | `LAYOUT.stackGap` (`gap-2`) | Vertical stacks inside a panel |
| Panel section | `LAYOUT.panelSection` | Header rows inside `TrackingGlassCard` |
| Panel block | `LAYOUT.panelBlock` | Filter / form blocks inside cards |
| Map above fold | `LAYOUT.mapAboveFoldHeight` + `LAYOUT.mapAboveFoldMin` | **Any map stage that has widgets below** (insights, actions, tables, playback footer) |
| Map stage wrapper | `TrackingMapStage` from `@/features/live-tracking/tracking-shell` | Map + optional footer widgets in document flow — **never absolute overlay on map bottom** |

**Never** use arbitrary gaps like `gap-4`, `gap-6`, or `space-y-6` on command-center split layouts. Live and History must share the same **`TrackingGlassCard`** sidebar shell.

---

## 4. Iconography

- Lucide icon on every chip, toggle, and semantic field label.
- Section headers: **`SectionHeading`** with tinted icon chip (Identity=primary, Assignment=violet, Operations=amber, Documents=emerald).

---

## 5. Color — semantic, for STATE

**Squint test:** In any group of toggles/chips, selected items must pop in under 1 second. If selected ≈ unselected, it fails.

### Toggle chips & multi-select pills (assets, tags, filters)

Use **`ToggleChip`** from `@/components/app/toggle-chip`. **Never `primary/10` for selected toggles.**

| State | Classes |
|-------|---------|
| **Selected / on** | `border-emerald-500 bg-emerald-100 text-emerald-900 ring-1 ring-emerald-400/50 font-semibold shadow-sm` + **`Check` icon** |
| **Unselected / off** | `border-border bg-muted/30 text-muted-foreground` + category icon at 60% opacity |

`primary/10` is for **metadata badges and links**, not toggle selection in a group.

### Single-choice segments (Active / Inactive)

- **Active / success option when selected:** same emerald stack as above (`SegmentOption variant="success"`).
- **Other selected segment:** `border-primary bg-primary/15 text-primary`.
- **Unselected:** muted outline.

### Other state colors

- **Uploaded document / success file row:** `border-emerald-200 bg-emerald-50 text-emerald-700`.
- **Required fields:** red `*` via `text-destructive`.
- **Avatar:** deterministic tint from name — never flat grey.
- **Driver ID badge:** `bg-primary/10 text-primary border-primary/20`.

Grey-on-grey everywhere = dead UI. **If the user provided a reference with green selected chips, match it exactly.**

When color intent is ambiguous, **ask** — do not default to muted primary.

---

## 6. Navigation — view page + add/edit modal

| Action | Pattern |
|--------|---------|
| **View / detail** (history, GPS, earnings, tabs) | Full page `/resource/[id]`. **List row click → detail page.** |
| **Add** | Modal on list via `?add=1` |
| **Edit** | Modal only — from detail page **Edit** button or `?edit=1` on detail URL. **Never from row click.** |

- `/resource/new` → redirect to list `?add=1`.
- **Do NOT** redirect `/resource/[id]` to the list.

List row: show subtle **"View details"** link under the name.

---

## 7. Footer-first modals (mandatory)

**Do not waste a top header band** for title/subtitle. Reclaim vertical space for content.

- **No top header** in modals. Content starts immediately (`pt-4`).
- **Close button: top-right, outside the modal frame** — use `DialogContent` with `showCloseButton` + `closeOutside` (floating circular X at `-end-3 -top-3`). **Never put Close in the footer.**
- **`AppModalFooter`** (`@/components/app/app-modal-footer`):
  - **Left**: **title** + **subtitle** (one line) + optional meta.
  - **Right**: Cancel + primary action.
- Title/subtitle use `DialogTitle` / `DialogDescription` for a11y.
- Large modals: `overflow-visible` on `DialogContent` when `closeOutside`; scroll only the inner body.

---

## 8. Action differentiation (mandatory)

Adjacent actions must never look identical. Users must instantly see **neutral vs destructive vs primary**.

| Action type | Style | Icon |
|-------------|-------|------|
| **View / open / link** | `text-primary hover:bg-primary/10` | `ExternalLink` |
| **Remove / delete / archive** | `text-destructive hover:bg-destructive/10` | `Trash2` |
| **Primary submit** | solid default button | — |
| **Cancel** | `variant="outline"` | — |

Never pair two plain `variant="ghost"` text buttons with the same size/color side by side.

---

## 9. No chrome inside modals

- No progress steppers, completion %, scroll-spy.
- Footer meta (e.g. draft saved) only when meaningful.

---

## 10. Reference images

Match density, column count, and architecture from user-provided screenshots. Ask before diverging.

---

## 11. Pre-ship checklist

- [ ] One viewport on 14" laptop — no inner scroll
- [ ] Footer-first modal: title in footer left, **Close top-right outside** (`closeOutside`)
- [ ] View vs Remove (or similar pairs) visually distinct with icons
- [ ] **Toggle chips:** selected = emerald green + check; unselected = muted (squint test)
- [ ] Section icon chips + tinted avatar + primary Driver ID badge
- [ ] Row click → detail page; edit → modal only
- [ ] Add via `?add=1` modal on list
- [ ] **Map above fold:** if any widgets/tables/actions sit below the map, use `TrackingMapStage` + `LAYOUT.mapAboveFoldHeight` — map must not overlap footer content
- [ ] Map markers and zones follow §12, including deselect paths

---

## 12. Maps & overlays

### Above-the-fold map stages (mandatory when widgets exist below)

If **anything** renders below the map — insights panels, quick actions, event tables, playback footers, KPI strips tied to the map — the map is a **stage**, not a full-page canvas.

| Rule | Detail |
|------|--------|
| **Use `TrackingMapStage`** | Map children inside the frame; footer widgets as the `footer` prop in normal document flow |
| **Cap map height** | `LAYOUT.mapAboveFoldHeight` + `LAYOUT.mapAboveFoldMin` (dynamic viewport fit; no fixed 560px cap) |
| **No bottom overlays** | Never `absolute bottom-*` widget grids on the map when those widgets can sit in `footer` |
| **Map fills frame only** | Inner map: `mapHeightClass="h-full min-h-0"` — do not add extra `min-h-[480px]` on the map itself |
| **Fullscreen exception** | Command fullscreen / map-only fullscreen may use `flex-1 h-full`; footer still below map, not overlaid |
| **Inline maps exempt** | Small contextual maps in sheets, tabs, or dashboard widgets (`h-44`–`h-64`) — fixed compact height is fine |
| **Side-by-side exempt** | Zone editor / list+map split views where the map shares a row with a sidebar — not a footer stack |

**Anti-patterns:** `min-h-[560px] flex-1` on a map frame with footer widgets; Fleet insights / Quick actions floating over the map bottom; history map taller than viewport while events table is below.

### Map behavior

- **Marker shape + icon:** use lucide-style vehicle icon inside a colored teardrop marker; status color comes from `pinStatus`.
- **Unknown vehicle default:** if vehicle type is missing, default to `bike`; never infer vehicle type from tracking status.
- **Zones:** render zone polygons/circles using the zone palette at `0.22` fill opacity and show a DOM label overlay (zone name + optional driver-count chip).
- **Driver deselect:** always support all three paths: popup close `X`, map background click, and clicking the same marker again.
- **Coming soon pills:** use small sentence-case `Coming soon` badges (`bg-amber-100 text-amber-800 border-amber-200`) only for missing backend-backed map/filter features.

---

## 13. Selects & Search

- Use `Select` only for small, fixed enums (status, tabs, static modes), typically <=30 options.
- Use `SearchSelect` for dynamic datasets (drivers, zones, partners, restaurants, users, and any list that can grow large).
- `SearchSelect` must provide:
  - contextual keywords (`name`, codes, IDs, mobile/email where relevant),
  - a `recentsKey` so the last 5-10 picks appear first on open,
  - contextual search placeholder text.
- Do not allow raw IDs in dropdown triggers. Triggers must always display a human-readable label.
